HEADWORD: Blackthorn
<hw>Black"thorn`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A spreading thorny shrub or small tree (<spn>Prunus
spinosa</spn>), with blackish bark, and bearing little black plums,
which are called sloes; the sloe.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A species of
<gen>Crat⟦ae⟧gus</gen> or hawthorn (<spn>Crat⟦ae⟧gus tomentosa</spn>).
Both are used for hedges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

